250 g Ground Pork
6 unit(s) Flour Tortillas
8 g Mexican Seasoning
6 tbsp Guacamole
½ cup Tomato Salsa
½ cup Cheddar Cheese, shredded
1 unit(s) Green Bell Pepper
0.06 tsp Pepper*
½ tbsp Oil*
0.06 tsp Salt*

Core, then cut pepper into 1/4-inch slices.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat. When hot, add 1/2 tbsp oil, then pork and peppers. Cook, breaking up pork into smaller pieces, until no pink remains, 4-5 min.**
Carefully drain and discard excess fat.
Add Mexican Seasoning. Cook, stirring often, until fragrant, 1 min.
Season with salt and pepper.

Divide tortillas between plates.
Top with pork and peppers, cheese, salsa and guacamole.